SIMPLE: pomp
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pomp
<hw>Pomp</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>pompe</ets>, F.
<ets>pompe</ets>, L. <ets>pompa</ets>, fr. Gr. <?/ a sending, a solemn
procession, pomp, fr. <?/ to send. Cf. <er>Pump</er> a shoe.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A procession distinguished by ostentation and splendor;
a pageant.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧All the <xex>pomps</xex> of a Roman
triumph.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Show of magnificence; parade; display;
power.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Display; parade; pageant; pageantry; splendor;
state; magnificence; ostentation; grandeur; pride.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pomp</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pomp
<hw>Pomp</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To make a pompous
display; to conduct.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>B.
Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pompadour</ent>⟦br⟧
